    <text id="B1205T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell reports no cases of unemployment among blacks in Augusta County,
                    although there are some cases in another Division of the Sub-District.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R. F. &amp; A.
                        L.</abbr><lb/>Head <abbr expan="Quarters">Qrs</abbr> 9th Sub <abbr
                            expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Brevet Brigadier General">Bt. Brig.
                        Gen.</abbr> O. Brown<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst
                        Comr</abbr>, Va<lb/>Richmond, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-12-31"><abbr expan="December">Dec.</abbr> 31s 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>General</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to report that in the 1st Division of this Sub District about
                    fifty able bodied freedmen, for whom employment cannot be found. In the other
                    Divisions the demand for labor is still equal to the supply.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obdt</abbr> Servant</salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> &amp; <abbr
                            expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">S.A.C.</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
